%N A391469 Number of words of length 3*n that can be formed with a three-letter alphabet when the number of letters of each type is == 1 (mod 3).
%C A391469 See comments in A391468.
%H A391469 Pablo Serra, <a href="/A391469/b391469.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..100</a>
%H A391469 Pablo Serra, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.22362">On the number of words of N = 3*M letters with a three-letter alphabet</a>, arXiv:2512.22362 [math.CO], 2025.
%H A391469 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (27,-27,729).
%F A391469 a(n) = Sum_{n1+n2+n3=n-1} trinomial(3 * n; 3 * n1 + 1,3 * n2 + 1, 3 * n3 + 1) for n>=1.
%F A391469 a(n) = 3^(3*n-2) - ((1 + (-1)^n) + (1 - (-1)^n)*i*sqrt(3))*i^n*3^((3*n-2)/2)/2 for n>=1, where i is the imaginary unit.
%F A391469 a(n) = 27*(a(n-1) - a(n-2) + 27*a(n-3)), for n >= 4.
%F A391469 G.f.: 6*x*(1 - 12*x - 27*x^2)/((1 - 27*x)*(1 + 27*x^2)).
%F A391469 a(n) + A391468(n) + A391470(n) + 2*A013733(n-1) = 3^(3*n) for n>=1.
%F A391469 E.g.f.: (2 + exp(27*x) - 3*cos(3*sqrt(3)*x) + 3*sqrt(3)*sin(3*sqrt(3)*x))/9. - _Stefano Spezia_, Dec 30 2025
%e A391469 For n=1, the a(1) = 6 words of length 3*n = 3 are ABC, CAB, BAC, CBA, BAC, CAB.
